  <article class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          After cleaning thousands of homes, we've learned that technique matters as much as effort. Clean the wrong way, and you're just moving dirt around. Clean the right way, and your home stays fresher, longer.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          This is the same room-by-room approach our professional cleaners use. Follow it, and you'll clean faster and more effectively than ever before.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Golden Rule: Top to Bottom, Back to Front</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
            Always clean from the ceiling down to the floor, and from the back of the room toward the door. Dust falls downward, and you don't want to walk through areas you've already cleaned.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Kitchen Cleaning Guide</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-4">
          The kitchen is usually the hardest room to clean properly. Grease, food particles, and moisture create a perfect storm for buildup.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">The Order That Works</h3>
        <ol class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Clear and declutter:</strong> Put away dishes, remove items from counters.</li>
          <li><strong>Appliances first:</strong> Microwave interior, oven exterior, refrigerator exterior. Let degreaser sit while you work elsewhere.</li>
          <li><strong>Upper cabinets:</strong> Wipe fronts and handles. Check tops if visible.</li>
          <li><strong>Countertops:</strong> Clear, spray, wipe. Move appliances to clean underneath.</li>
          <li><strong>Lower cabinets and drawers:</strong> Wipe fronts and handles.</li>
          <li><strong>Sink:</strong> Scrub basin, polish fixtures, wipe down disposal splash guard.</li>
          <li><strong>Stovetop:</strong> Remove grates, clean surface, replace grates.</li>
          <li><strong>Floor:</strong> Sweep first, then mop. Don't forget under the table and behind the trash can.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Spots Most People Miss</h3>
        <ul class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-2">
          <li>Top of the refrigerator</li>
          <li>Inside and around the trash can</li>
          <li>Light switches and cabinet handles</li>
          <li>Under the dish drying rack</li>
          <li>The range hood filter</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Bathroom Cleaning Guide</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Bathrooms need both cleaning AND disinfecting. These are two different steps.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">The Order That Works</h3>
        <ol class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Apply toilet bowl cleaner:</strong> Let it sit while you clean everything else.</li>
          <li><strong>Spray shower/tub:</strong> Let product work while you continue.</li>
          <li><strong>Dust vents and light fixtures:</strong> Start high.</li>
          <li><strong>Clean mirrors:</strong> Spray, wipe in Z-pattern, buff dry.</li>
          <li><strong>Wipe counters and sink:</strong> Don't forget faucets and handles.</li>
          <li><strong>Scrub shower/tub:</strong> Focus on grout lines and fixtures.</li>
          <li><strong>Clean toilet:</strong> Outside first (lid, seat, base), then inside.</li>
          <li><strong>Floor:</strong> Start at far corner, work toward door.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Spots Most People Miss</h3>
        <ul class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-2">
          <li>Behind the toilet base</li>
          <li>Exhaust fan cover</li>
          <li>Inside the toilet brush holder</li>
          <li>Shower door tracks</li>
          <li>Cabinet interior shelves</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Bedroom Cleaning Guide</h2>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">The Order That Works</h3>
        <ol class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Strip the bed:</strong> Wash sheets in hot water weekly.</li>
          <li><strong>Declutter surfaces:</strong> Nightstands, dressers, windowsills.</li>
          <li><strong>Dust from top:</strong> Ceiling fan, light fixtures, top of furniture.</li>
          <li><strong>Dust middle:</strong> Furniture surfaces, picture frames, mirrors.</li>
          <li><strong>Make the bed:</strong> Fresh sheets create that "clean room" feeling.</li>
          <li><strong>Vacuum or mop:</strong> Include under the bed and in closet.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Spots Most People Miss</h3>
        <ul class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-2">
          <li>Top of ceiling fan blades</li>
          <li>Under the bed</li>
          <li>Top of door frames</li>
          <li>Lamp shades</li>
          <li>Baseboards behind furniture</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Living Room Cleaning Guide</h2>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">The Order That Works</h3>
        <ol class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Pick up and organize:</strong> Return items to their places.</li>
          <li><strong>Dust high:</strong> Ceiling corners, light fixtures, top shelves.</li>
          <li><strong>Dust entertainment center:</strong> Don't forget behind and around electronics.</li>
          <li><strong>Clean glass:</strong> TV screen (with appropriate cleaner), mirrors, picture glass.</li>
          <li><strong>Furniture:</strong> Vacuum upholstery, fluff pillows, straighten cushions.</li>
          <li><strong>Dust low:</strong> Coffee tables, end tables, baseboards.</li>
          <li><strong>Floor:</strong> Vacuum thoroughly, including edges and under furniture.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Spots Most People Miss</h3>
        <ul class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 space-y-2">
          <li>Remote controls</li>
          <li>Under couch cushions</li>
          <li>Light switch plates</li>
          <li>Behind the TV</li>
          <li>Window sill dust</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">How Often Should Each Room Be Cleaned?</h2>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
